Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.75,0:00:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It is interesting that Peter gives counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.42,0:00:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,about cultivating humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.79,0:00:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn the clock back
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.12,0:00:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn why the quality of humility
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.63,0:00:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was indelibly etched
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.60,0:00:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mind and heart of Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.46,0:00:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s open our Bibles to Luke chapter 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.10,0:00:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In Luke chapter 22,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.14,0:00:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll find Jesus getting ready\Nfor that final Passover in 33 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.74,0:00:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And in Luke 22, starting in verse 8,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.41,0:00:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it is Thursday afternoon, Nisan 13,\Nand what happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.42,0:00:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 8: “Jesus sent Peter [there he is]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.02,0:00:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“and John, saying: ‘Go and get
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.22,0:00:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the Passover ready for us to eat.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.36,0:00:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Get it ready, Peter and John.’
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.76,0:00:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 9: “They said to him:\N‘Where do you want us to get it ready?’”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.53,0:00:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They understood the instructions: Get it ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.84,0:00:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said to go into Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.84,0:00:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll find the man\Nwith the earthenware jar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.68,0:01:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 12: “And that man
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.71,0:01:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“will show you\Na large, furnished upper room.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.91,0:01:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it ready there.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.52,0:01:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 13: “So they left \Nand found it just as he had told them,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.79,0:01:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and they prepared for the Passover.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.33,0:01:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it ready; prepare the Passover.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.43,0:01:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What would that include?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.83,0:01:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Bread, wine, oil for the lamps,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.87,0:01:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,lamb, a towel, a basin, water.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.88,0:01:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Basin and water
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.55,0:01:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—they knew \Nhow important washing feet was.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.38,0:01:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They witnessed when\NJesus reproved Simon the Pharisee
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.05,0:01:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,with the statement: Simon,\N“you gave me no water for my feet.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.42,0:01:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Simon, you gave me no water.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.49,0:01:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You missed the mark on this one.’
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.03,0:01:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So as they stared\Nat that basin and water,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.43,0:02:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as they prepared\Nand got the room ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.24,0:02:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,did they look at each other\Nand wonder:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who’s going to wash the feet?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.78,0:02:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’s going to do it?’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.58,0:02:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They had a golden opportunity\Nto apply all the things that Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.31,0:02:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,had been teaching them\Nfor three and a half years on humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.42,0:02:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,After three and a half years,\Nconduct yourself as a lesser one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.22,0:02:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t lord it over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.02,0:02:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to serve others and not be served.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.56,0:02:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This was it; this was the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.56,0:02:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They could have showed Jesus\Nthat they got the point; they got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.27,0:02:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They had time to think about it\Nand time to pray about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.27,0:02:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Thursday afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.17,0:02:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but now we progress\Nand let’s see what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s now progress \Nto the evening, and it’s Nisan 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.75,0:02:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s pick up the account in John chapter 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They got the room ready,\Nthey followed the instructions,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.15,0:02:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and now let’s go to John 13\Nand get John’s vantage point from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.96,0:02:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He was there;\Nhe was with Peter getting it ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.00,0:03:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So now it’s 98 C.E.,\Nand John is writing this information.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.00,0:03:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He had time to reflect\Nand to think about this for years,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.04,0:03:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and now look what he says in verse 3:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.77,0:03:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.34,0:03:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“knowing that the Father\Nhad given all things into his hands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.78,0:03:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he came from God\Nand was going to God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.72,0:03:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing these things\N—he understood that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.62,0:03:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He sat back and said:\N‘Jesus knew who he was; he knew all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He had the full understanding of his dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.03,0:03:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew that he\Nhad been entrusted with all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.97,0:03:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.20,0:03:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew he was the second greatest\Npersonage in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.20,0:03:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew he was\N“the firstborn of all creation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He knew he had\Nshared with his Father in creating all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He had knowledge of all this\N—knowing all these things.’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.01,0:03:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,John sits back; he writes this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.05,0:03:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then knowing this,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.39,0:03:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 4 is the contrast:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.46,0:04:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He got up from the evening meal\Nand laid aside his outer garments.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.46,0:04:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Taking a towel,\Nhe wraps it around his waist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‘After that, he puts the water\Ninto the basin
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.83,0:04:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and starts to wash\Nthe feet of the disciples
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.73,0:04:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and dry them off with the towel\Nthat was wrapped around him.’
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.84,0:04:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing who He was,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.34,0:04:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,John said He did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.54,0:04:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But not only does John reflect\Non who Jesus was,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,no, he reflects on why Jesus did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.32,0:04:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.42,0:04:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what John was interested in,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and we get that answer back in verse 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.03,0:04:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where John says why:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.16,0:04:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Because he loved his own\Nthat were in the world;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.23,0:04:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,he loved them to the end.’
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.20,0:04:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,John said He “loved them to the end.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.10,0:04:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.51,0:04:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to instill in them qualities\Nthat would help them conquer the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.48,0:04:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities that would strengthen\Nthe Christian congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.95,0:05:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities such as unselfish love\Nand humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.05,0:05:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He loved them to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He never gave up on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.05,0:05:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They had their weaknesses,\Nbut he did not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.92,0:05:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for Peter, some 30 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.16,0:05:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s thinking about humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.43,0:05:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,John, some 60 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.80,0:05:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,after the lesson Jesus taught\Nabout humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.27,0:05:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s echoing loud and clear\Nin his mind and heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.04,0:05:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the fact remains\Nthat neither of them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.44,0:05:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,had the humility at the time\Nto apply what Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.71,0:05:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,had been teaching them\Nfor three and a half years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.05,0:05:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after John finished his writing, he sat back;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.92,0:05:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,he was under inspiration;\Nhe finished that writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.92,0:05:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he sit back,\Nreread what he just wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.03,0:05:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps say to himself:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.70,0:05:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I wish I could have written
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.20,0:05:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that after Jesus washed the feet\Nof one or two of his disciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I got up and washed the feet
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.01,0:06:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,‘of the rest of my brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.18,0:06:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I took that towel, and I imitated the Christ?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.78,0:06:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, Peter and I got up?’
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But the point is, they didn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.79,0:06:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we learn?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.82,0:06:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t allow valuable lessons\Nthat Jesus teaches us
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.56,0:06:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to echo in our minds and hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.70,0:06:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,only after we missed\Nthe opportunity to apply them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a practical setting\Nfor us serving here at Bethel:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.51,0:06:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Even though I know\NI have the seniority
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.74,0:06:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‘—I have full knowledge of my seniority—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.55,0:06:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‘will I get up and fight the attitude\Nof entitlement?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know I have\Nauthority entrusted to me as the overseer;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.36,0:06:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I am the overseer;\NI know that. I have full knowledge of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.66,0:06:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Fine, will I get up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.30,0:06:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and roll my sleeves back\Nand do the grunt work?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:06:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Or do I just find pleasure\Nin giving orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know I have\Na wonderful privilege of service;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.74,0:07:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know that; others know it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.44,0:07:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, but will I get up to train others?’
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.61,0:07:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Jackson reminded us of this\Nat the last Gilead graduation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.98,0:07:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,when he said to treasure your privileges,\Nbut don’t hoard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we have to get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.39,0:07:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes humility \Nto train others to take our place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.26,0:07:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‘As a brother or a sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.16,0:07:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know I have more experience\Nthan the other person in my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.04,0:07:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know I have the experience; I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I have more experience than my workmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.91,0:07:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Fine, but will I get up in all humility
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and share information that I have
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.78,0:07:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,‘with others to make their job easier?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Or will I hold the knowledge I have hostage?’
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.82,0:07:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get up in all humility\Nand do these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:08:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can say that Jesus’ humble act,\Nas recorded here in John 13,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.30,0:08:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,has made a lasting\Nand indelible impression
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.14,0:08:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,not only on Peter and John\Nbut on me.
